# Environment Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env to version control!

# ====================================================================
# Cloudflare Worker Environment Variables (set via Cloudflare Dashboard)
# ====================================================================
# These are NOT used by the frontend. They must be set in your
# Cloudflare Worker environment variables or .dev.vars file.
#
# DS_KEY — DeepSeek API Key (get from: https://platform.deepseek.com/api-keys)
# ALLOWED_ORIGIN — Your domain, e.g. https://mpalomaresdigitalsolutions.site
# TURNSTILE_SECRET — Cloudflare Turnstile secret key
#
# See: workers/chat-proxy.js and wrangler.toml

# ====================================================================
# Frontend Configuration (set in index.html)
# ====================================================================
#
# 1. PROXY_URL — Your deployed Cloudflare Worker URL
#    Example: https://chat-proxy.your-subdomain.workers.dev
#    (search for "PROXY_URL" in index.html)
#
# 2. TURNSTILE_SITEKEY — Cloudflare Turnstile site key (public)
#    Get yours at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/?to=/:account/turnstile
#    (search for "TURNSTILE_SITEKEY" in index.html)
#
# 3. SHEET_URL — Google Apps Script endpoint for saving contact form data.
#    This is obfuscated in index.html and is optional.

# Instructions:
# 1. Get a DeepSeek API key from: https://platform.deepseek.com/api-keys
# 2. Create a Cloudflare Turnstile widget and get site key + secret key
# 3. Deploy the Cloudflare Worker (see workers/chat-proxy.js)
# 4. Set DS_KEY, ALLOWED_ORIGIN, TURNSTILE_SECRET in Cloudflare Worker dashboard
# 5. Set PROXY_URL and TURNSTILE_SITEKEY in index.html
# 6. Add the proxy domain to the CSP connect-src in index.html
# 7. Never share your DS_KEY or .env file
